        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued May 17 at 3:54PM EDT until May 17 at 4:45PM EDT by NWS Albany NY</headline>
        <description>SVRALY

The National Weather Service in Albany has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Central Warren County in east central New York...
Northeastern Fulton County in eastern New York...
Northwestern Saratoga County in east central New York...
West central Washington County in east central New York...

* Until 445 PM EDT.

* At 351 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over Edinburg, or
15 miles northeast of Gloversville, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Hail damage to vehicles is expected. Expect wind damage
to roofs, siding, and trees.

* Locations impacted include...
Thurman Station, Cleverdale, Beartown, Tenantville, Sweets
Crossing, Shaw Corners, Lake Luzerne, Barkersville, South Bay
Village, Glenwild, Wiley Corners, Conklingville, Warrensburg,
Oneida Corners, Carpenters Corners, Paradise Beach, Osbourne
Bridge, Riverbank, Corinth, and West Day.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

Large hail, damaging wind, and continuous cloud to ground lightning
are occurring with this storm. Move indoors immediately. Lightning is
one of nature's leading killers. Remember, if you can hear thunder,
you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
